<br>
Upon being accused of such slander he instantly moves online to the AD board to put an end to said slander.<br>
<br>
As far as the morality of being friends with a PK or sitting and talking with an old friend.  I never really cared much about those screenshots(Once) obviously, seeing how I never posted them until war and MiM was behaving like hypocrits.  I already knew that Isildr, Zayda, and Once go way back.  Early on in EQ Once was a member of the Anti-PK guild Elven Brotherhood along with his good buddy and also later PK Laroux/Arews.<br>
<br>
However, if you want to talk to an &quot;old friend&quot; you can do so with /tells, a feature in the game which allows communication.  I have known people who have turned PK or were PKs that were a respected enemy that I would communicate in that manner, yet if I encountered them in a combat zone, I would attack, no questions or hesitation.<br>
<br>
That is supposed to be the &quot;morality&quot; of the server.  A PK is worldwide KoS.  There are some people who don't like PvP and thus try to avoid it, but avoiding PvP and doing nothing are entirely different.<br>
<br>
It was not my intent ever to try and get MiM in trouble.  Had I wanted to do that the second I took those screenshots I would of posted them with a &quot;OMG look at MIM with Darkenbane!!&quot;.  However, during the war when MiM strutted around acting high and mighty, filled with virtue, I posted those screens.  Some people in MiM have gone out of their way to try and depict us as scum, called us &quot;Pks&quot;, have used their propoganda to try and get us KoS to other guilds, and flat out have acted in dishonorable and devious behavior.  They contact people in other guilds who are either their friends or whom dislike Sadko to try and cause problems.<br>
<br>
If MiM was so virtuous, they would negotiate and end this war.  They would not make a small group of people who are Anti-PK permanent KoS.<br>
<br>
A little history.  While I know that most people hate Sadko, and MiM goes around calling us his &quot;followers&quot; or &quot;fanatics&quot; that is not true.  Most hatred about Sadko is based on rumors, stories they heard from someone else, one sided stories where people fail to take their own responsibility for how they were acting like a jerk at the time themselves, etc etc.  Are we loyal to one another?  Hell yes we are.  For the most part we have been gaming with one another for years, and it takes a long time before we completely trust someone new that we meet in EQ.  We know and trust and believe in one another and we will defend each other because nobody else knows our group, how we work, or our beliefs.<br>
<br>
When I first met Sadko it was in Diablo and I was a member of Inferno, a PK guild.  My name in game was Tracy Lords(teen porn star and hence my nickname of TL).  I was one of the most notorious anti-cheating PKers in that game and guess what...Sadko was an Anti-PK hunting me down.  I thought he was a dick asshole, he thought the same of me, and we fought all the time.  Eventually through mutual respect we became friends.<br>
<br>
Through UO we were just PvPers, not Pks, not really Anti-PK, mainly Anti-Dickhead, a belief I picked up from my friends in The Fuckheads whom I met in Beta and fought.  UO was a lot different than EQ in terms of PvP though, and many times it was one big war zone.  Most of the guilds we fought with or against moved into EQ.  Our guild was Priests of Chaos, when we moved from Atlantic Server some of us stayed and joined Covetous Crew(Dolza and Angus if anyone remember them).  Other guilds around were Pluggers, The Mercs, Pirates of Dark Water, The Regulators, LLTS, AoD, many guilds that made the transition over to EQ in the begining.  For the most part we had friends and enemies scattered through many different guilds with different beliefs.  When I started in EQ, I set my slate to Anti-PK, because the PKs of Everquest disgusted me and the way they fought was cowardly, more concernded with making sure they can run away and live than actually fighting, and in Diablo and UO it was fight to the death(majority of the time I PvP in EQ I do not have gate spell up).<br>
<br>
Through all this time and changes through games I know Sadko to be a firm Anti-PKer.  Yes, he is a different, he is a Russian heathen after all, and yes he will stand up for himself and his friends and he will be wary of the intentions of people he does not trust, and I will be the first to admit he can sound like an ass.  However, if you are his friend you will know it, and respect the fact that he would thus do anything to help you out.  That is the reason until the end I would fight side by side with my pals, and instead of calling us &quot;pks&quot; MiM should respect us for those reasons to why we do not crumble.<br>
<br>
TL<br>
<br>
ps. sorry for lenghty post I am a writer and extremely bored.  time for bf1942.<br>
